  "function_name": "handleAssignment",
  "justification": "This method reconciles the stream processing task manager's current task ownership with a new assignment after rebalance. It takes two maps (activeTasks and standbyTasks) mapping TaskIds to TopicPartition sets. The method: (1) logs the delta between existing and new assignments via log.info(), (2) registers subscribed topics from active partitions via topologyMetadata.addSubscribedTopicsFromAssignment(), (3) creates mutable copies of assignment maps and empty collections for tasksToRecycle and tasksToCloseClean, (4) locks tasks appearing in both old and new assignments via maybeLockTasks(), (5) iterates over all existing tasks deciding their fate - if a task ID is in new active set and already active, it updates input partitions and resumes; if standby but needs to become active (or vice versa), marks for recycling; tasks not in either map are marked for clean closure, (6) closes and recycles tasks via closeAndRecycleTasks(), (7) unlocks tasks via maybeUnlockTasks(), (8) aggregates exceptions with prioritization (fatal > migrated > corrupted) in maybeThrowTaskExceptions(), and (9) creates brand-new tasks for remaining IDs via createNewTasks(). The method returns void and has side effects of updating internal task registries as described."
}

